<h2>Hamas: new common pit in Al-Shifa, exhumed 49 bodies</h2>
The Hamas> government in the Gaza Strip has identified a new common pit > from which 49 bodies have already been exhumed in the Al Shifa hospital. The authorities of Gaza state that rescue teams continue to dissuade the bodies and expect to find "new bodies" in the common pit, the third found in the hospital center from which about 400 deaths have already been recovered, according to a statement. During operations at the hospital, Israel claimed to have killed some 200 alleged militants and questioned more than 800 suspects, including identifying about 500 members of Hamas and Palestinian Islamic Jihad, including senior officials. So far, according to Hamas, seven common pits were found in the Gaza Strip hospitals, three of which in Naser, three Khan Yunis (south) and another in the Kamal Adwan hospital (north).
